nt|For Brad and me a 1NT response was a viable option. One of the big problems with 2/1 Game Force is that the system does not deal with invitational hands very well. Brad and I play some fancy conventions that give us the ability to show both invitational and signoff hands in either minor after a 1NT response, but there were 2 reasons why I rejected this call.|
pg| ***** 6 ***** |


nt|First, as a 1NT response is semi-forcing, Brad could pass. I suspected that 1NT was not where I wanted to play on this deal. The other reason why I rejected a 1NT response was that this call makes it impossible to find a 4-4 spade fit (unless Brad is strong enough to reverse into 2@S at his next turn).|
